         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="subfield"><strong>$8 - Field link and sequence number</strong> 
        <div class="description">See description of this subfield in Appendix A: <em><a href="//www.loc.gov/marc/bibliographic/ecbdcntf.html">Control
                                       Subfields</a></em>.
        </div>
   </div>
      <hr>
      <h3>INPUT CONVENTIONS</h3>
      <div class="description2"><strong>Punctuation</strong> -  Field 555 ends with a period unless another mark of punctuation is present.
      </div>
      <div class="description2"><strong>Display Constants</strong> - Introductory terms or phrases such as <em>Indexes:</em> are not carried in the MARC
                     record. They may be system generated as display constants associated with the first
                     indicator value.
         <div class="table">
            <table>
               <tr>
                  <td width="135" align="left" valign="top"><u>First indicator</u></td>
                  <td width="336" align="left" valign="top"><u>Display constant</u></td>
               </tr>
               <tr>
                  <td valign="top" align="left">#</td>
                  <td valign="top" align="left">Indexes:</td>
               </tr>
               <tr>
                  <td valign="top" align="left">0</td>
                  <td valign="top" align="left">Finding aids:</td>
               </tr>
               <tr>
                  <td valign="top" align="left">8</td>
                  <td valign="top" align="left"><em>[no display constant]</em></td>
               </tr>
            </table>
         </div>
      </div>
      <hr>
      <h3>CONTENT DESIGNATOR HISTORY</h3>
      <div class="font_small">Archival and manuscripts control records created prior to 1983 may contain coded
                     information related to finding aids in obsolete field 008/34 (Level of collection
                     control code).<br>
   <br><em>$u - Uniform Resource Identifier [NEW, 2000]</em></div>
